105     #ifdef RC_ADJUST
106     static size_t rc_adjust_yystype(void *x, int by) 
107     {
108       struct yystype *p = x;
109       RC_ADJUST_PREAMBLE;
110     
111       RC_ADJUST(p->u.ptr, by);
112       RC_ADJUST(p->idtoken.location.filename, by);
113       RC_ADJUST(p->idtoken.id.data, by);
114       RC_ADJUST(p->idtoken.decl, by);
115     
116       return sizeof *p;
117     }
118     
119     static void rc_update_yystype(struct yystype *old, struct yystype *new)
120     {
121       regionid base = regionidof(old);
122     
123       RC_UPDATE(base, old->u.ptr, new->u.ptr);
124       RC_UPDATE(base, old->idtoken.location.filename, new->idtoken.location.filename);
125       RC_UPDATE(base, old->idtoken.id.data, new->idtoken.id.data);
126       RC_UPDATE(base, old->idtoken.decl, new->idtoken.decl);
127     }
128     #endif

130     /* A stack of declspecs and attributes for use during parsing */
131     typedef struct spec_stack *spec_stack;
132     struct spec_stack { 
133       type_element parentptr declspecs;
134       attribute parentptr attributes;
135       spec_stack sameregion next;
136     };
137     
138     /* Stack of saved values of current_declspecs and prefix_attributes.  */
139     /* In an ideal world, we would be able to eliminate most rc ops for
140        declspec_stack and ds_region assignments. Seems tricky though. */
141     static spec_stack declspec_stack;
142     static region ds_region;
143     
144     /* Pop top entry of declspec_stack back into current_declspecs,
145        prefix_attributes */
146     static void pop_declspec_stack(void) deletes
147     {
148       current_declspecs = declspec_stack->declspecs;
149       prefix_attributes = declspec_stack->attributes;
150       declspec_stack = declspec_stack->next;
151       if (!declspec_stack)
152         deleteregion_ptr(&ds_region);
153     }
154     
155     static void push_declspec_stack(void)
156     {
157       spec_stack news;
158     
159       if (!ds_region) ds_region = newsubregion(parse_region);
160       news = ralloc(ds_region, struct spec_stack);
161       news->declspecs = current_declspecs;
162       news->attributes = prefix_attributes;
163       news->next = declspec_stack;
164       declspec_stack = news;
165     }

1497     /* Copy COUNT objects from FROM to TO.  The source and destination do
1498        not overlap.  */

1500     #  if 1 < __GNUC__

1503     #  else

1505           do					\
1506     	{					\
1507     	  register YYSIZE_T yyi;		\
1508     	  for (yyi = 0; yyi < (Count); yyi++)	\

1510     	}					\
1511           while (0)

1515     /* Relocate STACK from its old location to the new one.  The
1516        local variables YYSIZE and YYSTACKSIZE give the old and new number of
1517        elements in the stack, and YYPTR gives the new location of the
1518        stack.  Advance YYPTR to a properly aligned location for the next
1519        stack.  */
1520     # define YYSTACK_RELOCATE(Stack)					\
1521         do									\
1522           {									\
1523     	YYSIZE_T yynewbytes;						\
1524     	YYCOPY (&yyptr->Stack, Stack, yysize);				\
1525     	Stack = &yyptr->Stack;						\
1526     	yynewbytes = yystacksize * sizeof (*Stack) + YYSTACK_GAP_MAX;	\
1527     	yyptr += yynewbytes / sizeof (*yyptr);				\
1528           }									\
1529         while (0)

1741     /* YY_DECL_VARIABLES -- depending whether we use a pure parser,
1742        variables are global, or local to YYPARSE.  */
1743     
1744     #define YY_DECL_NON_LSP_VARIABLES			\
1745     /* The lookahead symbol.  */				\
1746     int yychar;						\
1747     							\
1748     /* The semantic value of the lookahead symbol. */	\
1749     YYSTYPE yylval;						\

1757     						\
1758     /* Location data for the lookahead symbol.  */	\
1759     YYLTYPE yylloc;

1761     # define YY_DECL_VARIABLES			\

1769     YY_DECL_VARIABLES

1771     
1772     int
1773     yyparse (YYPARSE_PARAM_ARG)
1774          YYPARSE_PARAM_DECL
1775     {
1776       /* If reentrant, generate the variables here. */
1777     #if YYPURE
1778       YY_DECL_VARIABLES
1779     #endif  /* !YYPURE */
1780     
1781       register int yystate;
1782       register int yyn;
1783       int yyresult;
1784       /* Number of tokens to shift before error messages enabled.  */
1785       int yyerrstatus;
1786       /* Lookahead token as an internal (translated) token number.  */
1787       int yychar1 = 0;
1788     
1789       /* Three stacks and their tools:
1790          `yyss': related to states,
1791          `yyvs': related to semantic values,
1792          `yyls': related to locations.
1793     
1794          Refer to the stacks thru separate pointers, to allow yyoverflow
1795          to reallocate them elsewhere.  */
1796     
1797       /* The state stack. */
1798       short	yyssa[YYINITDEPTH];
1799       short *yyss = yyssa;
1800       register short *yyssp;
1801     
1802       /* The semantic value stack.  */
1803       YYSTYPE yyvsa[YYINITDEPTH];
1804       YYSTYPE *yyvs = yyvsa;
1805       register YYSTYPE *yyvsp;
1806     
1807     #if YYLSP_NEEDED
1808       /* The location stack.  */
1809       YYLTYPE yylsa[YYINITDEPTH];
1810       YYLTYPE *yyls = yylsa;
1811       YYLTYPE *yylsp;
1812     #endif
1813     
1814     #if YYLSP_NEEDED
1815     # define YYPOPSTACK   (yyvsp--, yyssp--, yylsp--)
1816     #else
1817     # define YYPOPSTACK   (yyvsp--, yyssp--)
1818     #endif
1819     
1820       YYSIZE_T yystacksize = YYINITDEPTH;
1821     
1822     
1823       /* The variables used to return semantic value and location from the
1824          action routines.  */
1825       YYSTYPE yyval;
1826     #if YYLSP_NEEDED
1827       YYLTYPE yyloc;
1828     #endif
1829     
1830       /* When reducing, the number of symbols on the RHS of the reduced
1831          rule. */
1832       int yylen;
1833     
1834       YYDPRINTF ((stderr, "Starting parse\n"));
1835     
1836       yystate = 0;
1837       yyerrstatus = 0;
1838       yynerrs = 0;
1839       yychar = YYEMPTY;		/* Cause a token to be read.  */
1840     
1841       /* Initialize stack pointers.
1842          Waste one element of value and location stack
1843          so that they stay on the same level as the state stack.
1844          The wasted elements are never initialized.  */
1845     
1846       yyssp = yyss;
1847       yyvsp = yyvs;
1848     #if YYLSP_NEEDED
1849       yylsp = yyls;
1850     #endif
1851       goto yysetstate;
1852     
1853     /*------------------------------------------------------------.
1854     | yynewstate -- Push a new state, which is found in yystate.  |
1855     `------------------------------------------------------------*/
1856      yynewstate:
1857       /* In all cases, when you get here, the value and location stacks
1858          have just been pushed. so pushing a state here evens the stacks.
1859          */
1860       yyssp++;
1861     
1862      yysetstate:
1863       *yyssp = yystate;
1864     
1865       if (yyssp >= yyss + yystacksize - 1)
1866         {
